Package: datapond
Title: Simple Data Lake Infrastructure for R with DuckLake
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("Cathal", "Byrne", email = "cathal.byrne@cso.ie", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Provides a unified R interface for DuckLake, a modern data lakehouse
    format built on DuckDB. Supports ACID transactions, time travel queries,
    schema evolution, and Iceberg export for Spark/Trino compatibility. Features
    include multiple catalog backends (DuckDB, SQLite, PostgreSQL), Hive and bucket
    partitioning, data clustering, streaming via data inlining, and direct Arrow
    integration. Facilitates data sharing between teams with built-in governance,
    table/column documentation via SQL COMMENT, views and macros stored in the
    catalog, and access control via file system permissions.
